      "Stage: letting the goal settle and testing its felt rightness BEFORE planning begins. Homework is NOT action toward the goal — that's S10's territory. Homework IS: (a) read the goal statement aloud once a day at the same time (morning or before sleep); (b) notice resistance when it comes — physical tightness, avoidance, inner critic voices ('who am I to want this'); (c) notice energy when it comes — aliveness, leaning forward, possibility; (d) arrive at S9 able to say whether the goal feels MORE or LESS right after a week, and why. This is the critical filter — if the goal is wrong, we find out now, before we build plans on top of it. Never accept 'I'll start working on it' as this week's homework — that's what S10 is for. The work this week is living with it.",
